<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-05-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-05-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="629" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d629">
                    <head>No. 629.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago de
                                    Cuba</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-05-26"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 26,
                            1888</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi></p>
                    <p>Thompson, minister resident Hayti, telegraphs here by French cable:</p>
                    <p>“Advise Secretary State, Washington, send war vessel. Revolution imminent,
                        Port au Prince.”</p>
                    <closer><signed><persName><hi rend="smallcaps">Reimer.</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>